<!-- ===================================================
     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
==================================================== -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">Small suburb, peaceful streets, genuine upsizer appeal.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Middle Park is one of those suburbs that buyers encounter by accident and then cannot stop thinking about. Tucked between Jindalee and Riverhills in the Centenary corridor, approximately 14 kilometres west of the CBD, it is a small suburb in the literal sense: fewer streets, fewer properties, and significantly less transactional activity than its better-known neighbours. That scarcity is part of the appeal.
    </p>
<!-- APPRAISAL FORM -->
