<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">FAQ</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:2.5rem;">Common questions about Middle Park.</h2>
    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives property values in Middle Park?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Middle Park's value is driven by its small-suburb scarcity, elevated leafy streets and the privacy it offers relative to higher-profile western corridor addresses. Because Middle Park has fewer properties than Jindalee or Riverhills, turnover is low and genuine competition emerges when a well-presented home comes to market. Buyers are primarily upsizing families and downsizers seeking a quieter address in the Centenary corridor.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Middle Park?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Middle Park homes typically sell within 28 to 42 days when priced correctly for the suburb. The low supply of available homes means that a well-presented property often draws buyers who have been watching the suburb for an extended period and are ready to act. Campaign timing matters here: the small buyer pool means a well-run campaign that reaches active buyers early is especially valuable.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Middle Park?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Middle Park is one of Brisbane's quieter western suburbs. The internal streets are leafy and peaceful, with an established tree canopy and a mix of family homes and elevated properties. It sits between Jindalee and Riverhills, so residents have access to Jindalee's retail strip and Sinnamon Park shopping while enjoying a lower-traffic residential environment. The Centenary Motorway provides straightforward access to the CBD.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Middle Park a good suburb to buy in right now?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Middle Park offers a combination of scarcity, leafy character and western corridor proximity that is increasingly hard to find at this distance from the city. For buyers who value privacy and established streetscapes over suburb name recognition, it is a genuinely appealing address. The low turnover means opportunities to buy here are less frequent than in adjacent suburbs, which adds to its appeal for long-term ownership.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

